## Task 10: Box Model

**CSS Box Model**

The CSS box model represents each HTML element as a box, composed of four main components:

1.  **Content:** The actual content of the element.
2.  **Padding:** The space between the content and the border.
3.  **Border:** The outline surrounding the content and padding.
4.  **Margin:** The space outside the border, separating the element from other elements.

**Understanding the Box Model**

The box model affects the layout and spacing of elements on a web page. By understanding and manipulating its components, you can control the size, shape, and position of elements.

**Example:**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Box Model</title>
    <style>
        .box {
            width: 200px;
            height: 100px;
            border: 1px solid black;
            padding: 20px;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: lightblue;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="box">This is a box.</div>
</body>
</html>
```

**Explanation:**

- The `.box` element has a width of 200px, a height of 100px, a black border of 1 pixel, a padding of 20px on all sides, a margin of 20px around the element, and a light blue background color.

